@deftp Class <gnome-file-entry>
This @code{<gobject>} class defines the following properties:

@table @code
@item history-id
Unique identifier for the file entry. This will be used to save the history
list.

@item browse-dialog-title
Title for the Browse file dialog.

@item directory-entry
Whether the file entry is being used to enter directory names or complete
filenames.

@item modal
Whether the Browse file window should be modal.

@item filename
Filename that should be displayed in the file entry.

@item default-path
Default path for the Browse file window.

@item gnome-entry
GnomeEntry that the file entry uses for entering filenames. You can use this
property to get the GnomeEntry if you need to modify or query any of its
parameters.

@item gtk-entry
GtkEntry that the file entry uses for entering filenames. You can use this
property to get the GtkEntry if you need to modify or query any of its
parameters.

@item use-filechooser
Whether to use the new GtkFileChooser widget or the GtkFileSelection widget to
select files.

@item filechooser-action
The type of operation that the file selector is performing.

@end table

@end deftp

