@deffn Function gnome-file-entry-get-full-path  (self@tie{}@code{<gnome-file-entry>}) (file_must_exist@tie{}@code{bool}) @result{}@tie{} (ret@tie{}@code{mchars})
@deffnx Method get-full-path
@samp{gnome_file_entry_get_full_path} is deprecated and should not be used in
newly-written code.

Gets the full absolute path of the file from the entry. If @var{file-must-exist}
is false, nothing is tested and the path is returned. If @var{file-must-exist}
is true, then the path is only returned if the path actually exists. In case the
entry is a directory entry (see @code{<gnome-file-entry-set-directory-entry>}),
then if the path exists and is a directory then it's returned; if not, it is
assumed it was a file so we try to strip it, and try again. It allocates memory
for the returned string.

@table @var
@item fentry
The GnomeFileEntry widget to work with.

@item file-must-exist
boolean

@item ret
a newly allocated string with the path or NULL if something went wrong

@end table

@end deffn

